[2] Pennsylvania (Philadelphia)
Date: Sat 12 Oct 2019, 3:05 PM ET
Source: CNN [abridged, edited]
https://www.cnn.com/2019/10/12/health/measles-philadelphia-airport-trnd/index.html


If you visited the Philadelphia International Airport earlier this month, you may have been exposed to measles. The Pennsylvania Department of Health warned the public on [Fri 11 Oct 2019] that anyone who visited the airport on [2 or 3 Oct 2019] could have contracted the viral infection.

"The Department of Health is working with the county and municipal health departments to notify Pennsylvanians who were on flights with the suspected case, but other individuals may have been exposed at the airport during the identified times," Secretary of Health Rachel Levin said in a statement, adding, "however, if you have been properly immunized against measles, your risk of getting the disease is minimal."

An individual who is suspected of having measles was at the airport on both days and may have exposed other people, Levine said.

So far this year [2019], there have been 15 confirmed cases of measles in Pennsylvania. In the US, there have been more than 1200 cases, marking the greatest number of cases reported in the country since 1992.

[Byline: Alaa Elassar]

